WELCOME TO ST. GEORGE CLIFTON
We extend to you a warm and heartfelt Christian welcome. Our parish is dedicated to imitating the love and faithfulness of Jesus Christ by sharing the gospel with out words and living it with our lives. We seek to strengthen and encourage one another in the faith so that we may be equipped to welcome many more into our family as fellow disciples of Jesus Christ.

News and Events

Please visit our Facebook site for current news.

The Shrine of St. Nectarios
The Greek Orthodox Church of Saint George is home to the Shrine of Saint Nectarios the Wonderworker. Born as Anastasios Kephalas on October 1, 1846, Saint Nectarios became a prolific preacher and writer. In 1889 he was ordained Bishop of Pentapolis and then in 1904 established a monastery on the island of Aegina. He resided there until his repose on November 8, 1920. His Feast Day is November 9.
